The Kano ministry of health on Saturday night said the state recorded 10 new cases of the COVID-19, as confirmed cases now rise to 37. The ministry made this known on its verified Twitter handle @KNSMOH. “As at April 18, 2020; 10 new COVID-19 cases confirmed, total confirmed cases in Kano State is 37. “One COVID-19 death was recorded”.  To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .